on \"tsconfig.app.json\")\n\n[tsconfig.base.json](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/tsconfig.base.json \"tsconfig.base.json\")\n\n[tsconfig.base.json](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/tsconfig.base.json \"tsconfig.base.json\")\n\n[tsconfig.json](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/tsconfig.json \"tsconfig.json\")\n\n[tsconfig.json](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/tsconfig.json \"tsconfig.json\")\n\n[tsconfig.node.json](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/tsconfig.node.json \"tsconfig.node.json\")\n\n[tsconfig.node.json](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/tsconfig.node.json \"tsconfig.node.json\")\n\n[vite.config.ts](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/vite.config.ts \"vite.config.ts\")\n\n[vite.config.ts](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/vite.config.ts \"vite.config.ts\")\n\n[vitest.config.ts](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/vitest.config.ts \"vitest.config.ts\")\n\n[vitest.config.ts](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/vitest.config.ts \"vitest.config.ts\")\n\n[vitest.setup.ts](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/vitest.setup.ts \"vitest.setup.ts\")\n\n[vitest.setup.ts](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/vitest.setup.ts \"vitest.setup.ts\")\n\n[yarn.lock](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/yarn.lock \"yarn.lock\")\n\n[yarn.lock](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/yarn.lock \"yarn.lock\")\n\nView all files\n\n## Repository files navigation\n\n-   [README](#)\n-   [MIT license](#)\n\n[![](https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/9355208/395142426-0a81cdc1-d957-47a9-b151-f5571be0d038.png?jwt=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..dBqHDFUbDkZAD_X9Oh5-17XFZLrm2OSWtdG3hfg-NPw)](https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/9355208/395142426-0a81cdc1-d957-47a9-b151-f5571be0d038.png?jwt=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..dBqHDFUbDkZAD_X9Oh5-17XFZLrm2OSWtdG3hfg-NPw)\n\n# Frappe UI\n\n[](#frappe-ui)\n\n**Rapidly build modern frontends for Frappe apps**\n\n[![NPM Downloads](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/f8f36cdcab1fd578ca0ba5b8f89803bbfe2609accaa796edd13649639d914e26/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f6e706d2f646d2f6672617070652d75692e7376673f7374796c653d666c6174)](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/f8f36cdcab1fd578ca0ba5b8f89803bbfe2609accaa796edd13649639d914e26/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f6e706d2f646d2f6672617070652d75692e7376673f7374796c653d666c6174) [![Screenshot 2024-12-12 at 5 27 58 PM](https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/9355208/395147396-56800b45-2859-4dc5-92b8-e40959ce4902.png?jwt=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..6PqWjTWRVpVr3XxbVcgJdOYGC8uQCYZML89tQAX58pA)](https://ui.frappe.io)\n\n## Frappe UI\n\n[](#frappe-ui-1)\n\nFrappe UI provides a set of components and utilities for rapid UI development. Components are built using Vue 3 and Tailwind. Along with generic components like Button, Link, Dialog, etc., it also contains utilities for handling server-side data fetching, directives and utilities.\n\n### Motivation\n\n[](#motivation)\n\nIn 2019, I began building [Frappe Books](https://github.com/frappe/books) which had a new design. This led to the creation of small reusable components like Button, Dialog, and Card. Moving on to [Frappe Cloud](https://github.com/frappe/press) in 2020, I reused and evolved these components in the Frappe Cloud UI. In 2022, while starting a new project, I decided to extract these components into a standalone package to avoid repeating the copy-paste process. This package is now being developed alongside the [Gameplan](https://github.com/frappe/gameplan), continually adding generic components and utilities for frontend development.\n\n### Under the Hood\n\n[](#under-the-hood)\n\n-   [TailwindCSS](https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss): Utility first CSS Framework to build design system based UI.\n-   [Headless UI](https://github.com/tailwindlabs/headlessui): Unstyled and accessible UI components.\n-   [TipTap](https://github.com/ueberdosis/tiptap): ProseMirror based rich-text editor with a Vue API.\n-   [dayjs](https://github.com/iamkun/dayjs): Minimal javascript library for working with dates.\n\n## Links\n\n[](#links)\n\n-   [Documentation](https://ui.frappe.io)\n-   [Vite Plugins](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/vite/README.md)\n-   [Frappe UI Starter Boilerplate](https://github.com/netchampfaris/frappe-ui-starter)\n-   [Community](https://github.com/frappe/frappe-ui/discussions)\n\n## Usage\n\n[](#usage)\n\nnpm install frappe-ui\n# or\nyarn add frappe-ui\n\nNow, import the FrappeUI plugin and components in your Vue app's `main.js`:\n\nimport { createApp } from 'vue'\nimport { FrappeUI } from 'frappe-ui'\nimport App from './App.vue'\nimport './index.css'\n\nlet app \\= createApp(App)\napp.use(FrappeUI)\napp.mount('#app')\n\nIn your `tailwind.config.js` file, include the frappe-ui preset:\n\nmodule.exports \\= {\n  presets: \\[\n    require('frappe-ui/src/utils/tailwind.config')\n  \\],\n  ...\n}\n\nNow, you can import needed components and start using it:\n\n<template\\>\n  <button\\>Click me</button\\>\n</template\\>\n<script\\>\n  import { Button } from 'frappe-ui'\n  export default {\n    components: {\n      Button,\n    },\n  }\n</script\\>\n\n## Claude Code skill\n\n[](#claude-code-skill)\n\nFor AI coding agents (Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, etc.), Frappe UI ships an agent skill that teaches the agent the library's conventions — semantic Tailwind tokens, the `variant` + `theme` color axes, the `useCall` data-fetching composable, common UI recipes, and anti-patterns to avoid.\n\nInstall with [Vercel's `skills` CLI](https://github.com/vercel-labs/skills):\n\nnpx skills add https://github.com/frappe/frappe-ui/tree/main/skills/frappe-ui\n\nThe skill lives in [`skills/frappe-ui/`](/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/skills/frappe-ui) and is updated alongside the library.\n\n## Used By\n\n[](#used-by)\n\nFrappe UI is being used in a lot of products by [Frappe](https://github.com/frappe).\n\n-   [Frappe Cloud](https://frappecloud.com)\n-   [Gameplan](https://github.com/frappe/gameplan)\n-   [Helpdesk](https://github.com/frappe/helpdesk)\n-   [Frappe Insights](https://github.com/frappe/insights)\n-   [Frappe Drive](https://github.com/frappe/drive)\n-   [Frappe Builder](https://github.com/frappe/builder)\n\n  \n  \n\n [![Frappe Technologies](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/499fb6972227c1e5634a13bb22267b09a384e5e655828a49c9d74d59cdcba1e1/68747470733a2f2f6672617070652e696f2f66696c65732f4672617070652d626c61636b2e706e67)](https://frappe.io)\n\n## About\n\nA set of components and utilities for rapid UI development\n\n[ui.frappe.io](https://ui.frappe.io \"https://ui.frappe.io\")\n\n### Topics\n\n[vue](/topics/vue \"Topic: vue\") [frappe](/topics/frappe \"Topic: frappe\") [ui-components](/topics/ui-components \"Topic: ui-components\")\n\n### Resources\n\n[Readme](#readme-ov-file)\n\n### License\n\n[MIT license](#MIT-1-ov-file)\n\n### Uh oh!\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\n[Activity](/frappe/frappe-ui/activity)\n\n[Custom properties](/frappe/frappe-ui/custom-properties)\n\n### Stars\n\n[**942** stars](/frappe/frappe-ui/stargazers)\n\n### Watchers\n\n[**24** watching](/frappe/frappe-ui/watchers)\n\n### Forks\n\n[**322** forks](/frappe/frappe-ui/forks)\n\n[Report repository](/contact/report-content?content_url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Ffrappe%2Ffrappe-ui&report=frappe+%28user%29)\n\n## [Releases 1](/frappe/frappe-ui/releases)\n\n[\n\nv0.0.31 Latest\n\nJun 13, 2022\n\n\n\n](/frappe/frappe-ui/releases/tag/v0.0.31)\n\n## [Packages 0](/orgs/frappe/packages?repo_name=frappe-ui)\n\n### Uh oh!\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\n### Uh oh!\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\n## [Contributors](/frappe/frappe-ui/graphs/contributors)\n\n### Uh oh!\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\n## Languages\n\n-   [TypeScript 37.4%](/frappe/frappe-ui/search?l=typescript)\n-   [Vue 36.4%](/frappe/frappe-ui/search?l=vue)\n-   [Markdown 18.4%](/frappe/frappe-ui/search?l=markdown)\n-   [JavaScript 7.0%](/frappe/frappe-ui/search?l=javascript)\n-   Other 0.8%\n\n## Foo