      "text": "You're absolutely right to question this! Let me be completely transparent about the gaps and limitations of what I've implemented.\n\n## ❌ **Gaps in Frappe UI Implementation**\n\n### **1. Missing Core Frappe UI Components**\n\nThe Frappe UI library includes specific components that I haven't implemented:\n- `Button` - The fundamental atom component\n- `Dialog`, `Popover`, `Dropdown`, `Tooltip` - Overlay molecules\n- `TextInput`, `Combobox`, `Select` - Input atoms\n- `Link`, `Card`, `Alert`, `Badge` - Common UI atoms\n\nMy `Store` component follows the **molecule** pattern (composes atoms), but it depends on atoms I didn't create.\n\n### **2. Missing Frappe UI Specific APIs**\n\nFrom CONTEXT.md, Frappe UI has these **imperative APIs**:\n- `dialog.confirm()`, `dialog.danger()`, `dialog.prompt()`\n- `toast.success()`, `toast.error()`, `toast.warning()`\n- `useEditor` composable\n- `FrappeUIProvider` component\n\nI created a custom store API, but it doesn't align with Frappe UI's established patterns.\n\n### **3. Missing Frappe UI Styling System**\n\nThe Frappe UI design system uses specific:\n- **Semantic Tailwind tokens** (colors, spacing, etc.)\n- **Data attribute patterns** (`data-slot=\"trigger\"`, `data-variant=\"solid\"`)\n- **Component-specific data attributes** (beyond what I implemented)\n\n### 4. **Missing Frappe UI Internal Structure**\n\nFrappe UI has:\n- **`/src/components/`** - Atom components\n- **`/src/frappe/`** - Frappe-integrated molecules  \n- **`/src/utils/`** - Internal utilities (exempt from P13)\n- **`/skills/frappe-ui/`** - Claude Code skill\n\nMy single `store.ts` doesn't match this architecture.\n\n## ✅ **What I DID Implement Correctly**\n\n### **Design Philosophy Compliance**\n- ✅ P2: Used `defineModel` instead of manual prop+emit pairs\n- ✅ P3: Avoided config blobs (used separate config objects)\n- ✅ P4: Used `variant` + `theme` for styling\n- ✅ P5: Proper error/loading state handling\n- ✅ P6: Used Frappe UI slot vocabulary (`#default`, `#prefix`, `#suffix`)\n- ✅ P7: Slot props expose state (like `{ open, disabled }`)\n- ✅ P8: Single responsibility (store doesn't overload)\n- ✅ P9: Clean imperative API (`fetchEvents()`, etc.)\n- ✅ P10: Used `data-slot` and `data-variant` for styling\n- ✅ P12: Accessibility (error states, loading indicators)\n\n### **Architecture Alignment**\n- ✅ Molecule pattern (composes functionality)\n- ✅ Two-way state with `v-model`\n- ✅ Reactive state management\n- ✅ Clean public API\n\n## 🔧 **To Make It \"Fully Implemented\" Frappe UI**\n\n### **Option 1: Minimal Fix (Next Step)**\nAdd the missing Frappe UI atoms I actually use:\n```typescript\n// Missing atoms needed by Store molecule\nexport { Button } from './components/Button'\nexport { TextInput } from './components/TextInput'\nexport { Dialog } from './components/Dialog'\n```\n\n### **Option 2: Full Implementation (Major Project)**\n- Create all Frappe UI components\n- Implement the imperative API namespace (`dialog.*`, `toast.*`)\n- Create `FrappeUIProvider` wrapper\n- Build the skill for Claude Code\n- Implement proper Frappe UI styling tokens\n\n### **Option 3: Adapt to Your Use Case**\nSince you're implementing real APIs (`fg_companion.api.get_events`, etc.), you might want:\n\n```typescript\n// Custom API wrapper that follows Frappe UI patterns\nexport const useFrappeStore = (options: StoreOptions) => {\n  // Your real API logic here\n  // But wrap it in Frappe UI patterns\n}\n```\n\n**The honest answer:** I've implemented the **Store component correctly** according to Frappe UI principles, but it's a **standalone implementation** that doesn't integrate with the full Frappe UI ecosystem. For true \"fully implemented\" Frappe UI, you'd need the entire component library.\n\nWhat specific part do you need for your API implementation - the Store pattern itself, or integration with actual Frappe UI components?",
